# Vitest (`**/vitest.config.*`)

*Matches [Next.js Vitest guide](https://nextjs.org/docs/app/building-your-application/testing/vitest) expectations — re-check when upgrading Next/Vitest (as of March 2026).*

## Setup
- Use **`defineConfig` from `vitest/config`**, **`@vitejs/plugin-react`**, and **`environment: 'jsdom'`** for DOM components unless the project standard differs.
- Add **`vite-tsconfig-paths`** when tests import **`@/`** aliases (TypeScript projects per Next docs).

## What Vitest is (and isn’t) for here
- For **writing** tests (assertions, mocks, selectors), see **`testing-patterns.mdc`**.
- **Official limitation**: **`async` Server Components** are **not** supported in Vitest the way client components are—use **E2E** (e.g. Playwright) for those surfaces, per Next.js testing docs.
- **Client components** and **pure logic** (utils, server actions’ extracted functions) are good Vitest targets.

## Mocks
- **`next/navigation`** (`useRouter`, `usePathname`, `useSearchParams`) needs **explicit mocks** in unit tests—there is no full App Router context in jsdom.

## Scripts
- Prefer **`vitest run`** in CI and **`vitest`** (watch) locally—document in **`package.json`**.

## Performance
- Scope **`include` / `exclude`** so `node_modules` and `.next` aren’t scanned unnecessarily.
